Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.74,0:07:15.00,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So basically,\N{\rChinese}对了吧？所以基本上，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.06,0:07:19.92,English,,0,0,0,,landlords are a classic type of rent -seeking elite.\N{\rChinese}地主是典型的租金寻求精英。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.28,0:07:22.88,English,,0,0,0,,And so they don't really work, but\N{\rChinese}于是他们不真正工作，但……
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.88,0:07:26.02,English,,0,0,0,,they make a lot of money because they own the land, because\N{\rChinese}他们因为拥有土地而赚了很多钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:28.98,English,,0,0,0,,they control all the resources, because they control all the capital.\N{\rChinese}他们掌握所有资源，因为他们掌握所有资本。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.16,0:07:33.90,English,,0,0,0,,And that forces the mass to go into slavery, to go into debt, which is what's happening in America today.\N{\rChinese}于是大众被迫进入奴役、债务，这正是美国今天的现状。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.36,0:07:39.00,English,,0,0,0,,The problem with this is that everyone wants to be part of the elite.\N{\rChinese}问题是人人都想成为精英。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:43.34,English,,0,0,0,,And there are too many elite over time, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是又有太多的精英，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.44,0:07:46.66,English,,0,0,0,,So even though the elite have many, many kids,\N{\rChinese}所以即使精英有很多很多孩子，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.44,0:07:49.94,English,,0,0,0,,the power is a zero -sum game.\N{\rChinese}权力是零和游戏。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.98,0:07:54.44,English,,0,0,0,,It's a hierarchy. And so this leads to the idea of elite overproduction,\N{\rChinese}它是一个层级结构。于是这导致了精英过度生产的概念，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.88,0:07:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Elite overproduction.\N{\rChinese}好吧？精英过度生产。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.12,0:08:02.56,English,,0,0,0,,This is a term coined by the historian Peter Turchin,\N{\rChinese}这是历史学家彼得·图尔奇恩创造的术语。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:05.58,English,,0,0,0,,okay? And his theory is that\N{\rChinese}好吧？他的理论是……
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.58,0:08:08.72,English,,0,0,0,,you have turmoil, you have wars,\N{\rChinese}你有动荡，你就有战争，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.62,0:08:17.86,English,,0,0,0,,war, war,\N{\rChinese}战争，战争
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.32,0:08:19.94,English,,0,0,0,,war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war,\N{\rChinese}战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战,战
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.02,0:08:28.02,English,,0,0,0,,war, war,\N{\rChinese}战，战，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.02,0:08:31.82,English,,0,0,0,,war, war, war, war, war, war, war, war,\N{\rChinese}战，战，战，战，战，战，战，战，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.96,0:08:40.32,English,,0,0,0,,war okay\N{\rChinese}战争，好吗
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.32,0:08:43.34,English,,0,0,0,,so another saying this is that\N{\rChinese}于是又有人说这就是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.34,0:08:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,an empire over time becomes insular they don't care about what\N{\rChinese}一个帝国随着时间变得孤岛化，他们不关心外部世界的事；他们只关心华盛顿的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.04,0:08:50.38,English,,0,0,0,,happens outside the world all they care about is what happens in Washington DC\N{\rChinese}happens outside the world all they careabout is what happens in Washington DC
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:51.84,English,,0,0,0,,and\N{\rChinese}和
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.84,0:08:56.40,English,,0,0,0,,as a result they make a lot of stupid mistakes okay\N{\rChinese}于是他们犯了许多愚蠢的错误，好吗
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.10,0:09:01.38,English,,0,0,0,,right the last thing is death okay the problem with death is\N{\rChinese}好了，最后一件事是死亡，好吗？死亡的问题是
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.38,0:09:04.00,English,,0,0,0,,that if there are no consequences to your\N{\rChinese}如果你的行为没有后果的话
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:08.40,English,,0,0,0,,actions you become arrogant you become lazy\N{\rChinese}行动让你自大、懒惰
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.40,0:09:11.98,English,,0,0,0,,and you become incompetent okay\N{\rChinese}并且你变得无能，好吗
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.98,0:09:14.50,English,,0,0,0,,because you don't care it doesn't really matter\N{\rChinese}因为你不在乎，没什么大不了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.50,0:09:15.42,English,,0,0,0,,let's lease the idea\N{\rChinese}让我们租个想法
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.42,0:09:20.82,English,,0,0,0,,of hubris okay hubris\N{\rChinese}自大，好自大
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.82,0:09:25.26,English,,0,0,0,,is just blindness to your own arrogance of violent arrogance\N{\rChinese}只是对自己大而已的盲目，才是大而已的盲目
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.26,0:09:28.32,English,,0,0,0,,that makes you make silly mistakes\N{\rChinese}那使你犯愚蠢的错
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.32,0:09:30.60,English,,0,0,0,,but you don't recognize your mistakes and\N{\rChinese}但你却不认识自己的错误并且不断重复同样的错误，直至一辈又一辈，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.60,0:09:35.36,English,,0,0,0,,you keep on repeating the same mistakes throughout your life over and over again, right?\N{\rChinese}于是，帝国似乎无敌可战，看来是如此吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.44,0:09:39.16,English,,0,0,0,,So yes, it seems like the empire is invincible,\N{\rChinese}So yes, it seems like the empire is invincible,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.50,0:09:42.20,English,,0,0,0,,but if you actually think about it,\N{\rChinese}但如果你真正思考它，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.79,0:09:46.60,English,,0,0,0,,the empire, its advantages becomes over time,\N{\rChinese}帝国的优势随时间而增大，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.80,0:09:48.86,English,,0,0,0,,its disadvantages, which\N{\rChinese}它的劣势则随之而增大
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.86,0:09:52.34,English,,0,0,0,,will lead ultimately to its downfall, okay?\N{\rChinese}最终会导致其衰落，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.44,0:09:54.88,English,,0,0,0,,So the mass leads to inequality,\N{\rChinese}于是规模导致不平等，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.40,0:09:58.08,English,,0,0,0,,the organization leads to overproduction,\N{\rChinese}组织导致过度产出，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.28,0:10:01.58,English,,0,0,0,,which leads to factionalism, and death leads to hubris.\N{\rChinese}导致分裂，死亡则导致自大。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.32,0:10:05.24,English,,0,0,0,,That's why an empire must fall over time.\N{\rChinese}这就是帝国随时间必然衰落的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.50,0:10:08.38,English,,0,0,0,,But an empire cannot fall by itself.\N{\rChinese}但帝国本身并不能自衰落。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.58,0:10:12.66,English,,0,0,0,,It needs an enemy that forces it to collapse, okay?\N{\rChinese}它需要一个敌人来迫使它崩溃，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.26,0:10:16.72,English,,0,0,0,,And so what happens is that an enemy will emerge\N{\rChinese}于是发生的事是会出现一个敌人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.24,0:10:20.58,English,,0,0,0,,that will overwhelm the empire\N{\rChinese}这个敌人将会压倒帝国
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.58,0:10:25.02,English,,0,0,0,,because it is able to take advantage of the weaknesses of the empire,\N{\rChinese}因为它能利用帝国的弱点，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.22,0:10:27.34,English,,0,0,0,,right? And so\N{\rChinese}对吧？于是
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.34,0:10:30.10,English,,0,0,0,,what are the weaknesses of this empire?\N{\rChinese}这个帝国的弱点是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.64,0:10:33.48,English,,0,0,0,,Well, the first major weakness of this empire is that\N{\rChinese}好吧，这个帝国的第一个主要弱点是……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.48,0:10:36.04,English,,0,0,0,,the people aren't really motivated.\N{\rChinese}人们并不真正有动力。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.42,0:10:40.62,English,,0,0,0,,So you, as people, are really motivated, you have a huge advantage, okay?\N{\rChinese}所以你们，作为人民，真的很有动力，你们有很大的优势，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.82,0:10:46.74,English,,0,0,0,,We call this energy. All right?\N{\rChinese}我们把这叫做能量。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.68,0:10:50.52,English,,0,0,0,,Now, as an empire, you become insular.\N{\rChinese}现在，作为一个帝国，你变得孤岛化。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.90,0:10:53.46,English,,0,0,0,,You refuse to admit your mistakes.\N{\rChinese}你拒绝承认自己的错误。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.54,0:10:54.74,English,,0,0,0,,You refuse to learn from others.\N{\rChinese}你不愿意向他人学习。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.02,0:10:59.62,English,,0,0,0,,Well, if you are willing to admit your mistakes,\N{\rChinese}好吧，如果你愿意承认自己的错误，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.84,0:11:01.10,English,,0,0,0,,if you're willing to learn,\N{\rChinese}如果你愿意学习，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.10,0:11:04.76,English,,0,0,0,,if you're willing to promote the best\N{\rChinese}如果你愿意推广最优秀的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.76,0:11:08.12,English,,0,0,0,,and brightest, if you're willing to be meritocratic, you have a huge advantage, okay?\N{\rChinese}和最聪明的，若你愿意实行功绩制，你就拥有巨大的优势，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.30,0:11:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,And so this idea of openness.\N{\rChinese}于是这就是开放性的想法。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.68,0:11:15.04,English,,0,0,0,,Now, the last idea is this.\N{\rChinese}现在，最后一个想法是这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.34,0:11:17.10,English,,0,0,0,,An empire, it's fractured.\N{\rChinese}一个帝国，它已经分裂。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.78,0:11:20.52,English,,0,0,0,,So if you're able to maintain cohesion,\N{\rChinese}所以如果你能保持团结，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.28,0:11:26.28,English,,0,0,0,,if people are able to remain united, if they're able to have a common purpose,\N{\rChinese}如果人们能保持团结，若他们能有共同目标，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.50,0:11:30.20,English,,0,0,0,,they will be strong, okay? So,\N{\rChinese}他们就会强大，好的？所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.20,0:11:34.68,English,,0,0,0,,you know, if an enemy of the empire emerges with these three qualities, energy,\N{\rChinese}你知道，如果一个帝国的敌人出现并具备这三种特质，能量，
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:39.42,English,,0,0,0,,openness, and cohesion, this enemy will defeat the empire.\N{\rChinese}开放与团结，这个敌人将击败帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.32,0:11:42.12,English,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make sense, okay?\N{\rChinese}不太通顺，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.30,0:11:47.76,English,,0,0,0,,So what I want you to focus on as you follow the news in this war between United States\N{\rChinese}所以我想让你在关注这场美中战争的新闻时聚焦于此。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.76,0:11:49.34,English,,0,0,0,,and Iran is ask yourself a question.\N{\rChinese}伊朗也请你自己问一个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.26,0:11:54.66,English,,0,0,0,,Will Iran become an energetic, open, and cohesive society?\N{\rChinese}伊朗会成为一个充满活力、开放且团结的社会吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.56,0:11:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,Because if it does, it will become invincible.\N{\rChinese}如果是，它就会变得无敌可战。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.98,0:12:03.34,English,,0,0,0,,The empire won't change because of hubris.\N{\rChinese}帝国因自负而不变。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.82,0:12:05.48,English,,0,0,0,,It's too static.\N{\rChinese}它太静止。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.64,0:12:07.32,English,,0,0,0,,It's too stagnant, too bureaucratic.\N{\rChinese}它太停滞，太官僚。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.48,0:12:08.86,English,,0,0,0,,So the empire won't change.\N{\rChinese}于是帝国不变。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.14,0:12:11.22,English,,0,0,0,,The empire will not admit its own mistakes.\N{\rChinese}帝国不会承认自己的错误。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.16,0:12:13.66,English,,0,0,0,,And quite honestly, Iran,\N{\rChinese}而且，伊朗，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.02,0:12:17.26,English,,0,0,0,,because it's still a country of 92 million people,\N{\rChinese}因为它仍是一个9200万人的国家，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.50,0:12:21.14,English,,0,0,0,,it still suffers from issues of mass organization and death.\N{\rChinese}它仍然面临大规模组织与死亡问题，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.22,0:12:26.68,English,,0,0,0,,And so if it's able to transform itself into an energetic,\N{\rChinese}于是若它能把自己转变为充沛的国家，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.88,0:12:29.06,English,,0,0,0,,open, and cohesive society, then it will be invincible.\N{\rChinese}开放且团结的社会，便会无敌可战。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.06,0:12:31.58,English,,0,0,0,,It will triumph over America.\N{\rChinese}它将战胜美国。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.82,0:12:36.56,English,,0,0,0,,That is the fundamental question in this war, okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是这场战争的根本问题，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.80,0:12:40.70,English,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about America, its technology.\N{\rChinese}别担心美国的技术。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.20,0:12:42.98,English,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about the economy.\N{\rChinese}别担心经济。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.34,0:12:44.62,English,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about these things, okay?\N{\rChinese}别担心这些事，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.30,0:12:47.86,English,,0,0,0,,Just ask yourself one question.\N{\rChinese}只需问自己一个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.42,0:12:52.02,English,,0,0,0,,Is Iran transforming as a society?\N{\rChinese}伊朗正以社会的方式转型吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.28,0:12:54.44,English,,0,0,0,,Are people becoming much more motivated?\N{\rChinese}人们的积极性是否大幅提升？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.56,0:12:59.04,English,,0,0,0,,Are people in Iran learning from their mistakes?\N{\rChinese}伊朗人们在从错误中学习吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.06,0:13:02.18,English,,0,0,0,,And innovating and becoming resilient on the battlefield?\N{\rChinese}并在战场上创新并变得更有韧性吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.40,0:13:06.46,English,,0,0,0,,Are the Iranians sticking together as a people?\N{\rChinese}伊朗人们作为一个民族团结在一起吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.78,0:13:10.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because if the answer is yes to all three questions,\N{\rChinese}好的？因为如果对这三个问题都回答是，伊朗就会赢，美方就会输。好的？这样说对吗？没问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.74,0:13:13.76,English,,0,0,0,,then Iran will win and America will lose.\N{\rChinese}好的？因为如果对这三个问题都回答是，伊朗就会赢，美方就会输。好的？这样说对吗？没问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.58,0:13:17.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense? All right.\N{\rChinese}好的？因为如果对这三个问题都回答是，伊朗就会赢，美方就会输。好的？这样说对吗？没问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.84,0:13:19.86,English,,0,0,0,,So that's just a theory. So\N{\rChinese}于是这只是个理论。于是
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:23.50,English,,0,0,0,,let's now talk\N{\rChinese}接下来我们来聊聊
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.50,0:13:27.86,English,,0,0,0,,specifically about America and Iran, okay?\N{\rChinese}具体说说美国和伊朗，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.86,0:13:32.20,English,,0,0,0,,So America will have three\N{\rChinese}于是美国在这场战争中将拥有三大优势，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.20,0:13:36.70,English,,0,0,0,,major advantages in this war, okay?\N{\rChinese}这三大优势当然是，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.84,0:13:39.22,English,,0,0,0,,These three advantages are, of course,\N{\rChinese}These three advantages are, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.86,0:13:44.08,English,,0,0,0,,technology, propaganda,\N{\rChinese}技术，宣传，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.30,0:13:48.20,English,,0,0,0,,and\N{\rChinese}和
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.20,0:13:49.92,English,,0,0,0,,money, wealth.\N{\rChinese}金钱，财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.54,0:13:56.84,English,,0,0,0,,These are the three major strengths of the American empire.\N{\rChinese}这些是美国帝国的三大优势。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.86,0:14:01.12,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Technology is just what you see every day, right?\N{\rChinese}好的？技术就是你每天看到的东西，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.42,0:14:04.74,English,,0,0,0,,The satellites that are able to position,\N{\rChinese}能够定位的卫星，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.06,0:14:08.06,English,,0,0,0,,target these airplanes\N{\rChinese}目标这些飞机
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:12.22,English,,0,0,0,,that are the greatest war machines in the world.\N{\rChinese}它们是世界上最强大的战争机器。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.94,0:14:18.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So America is home to the greatest scientists,\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以美国是最伟大科学家的家园。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.36,0:14:21.12,English,,0,0,0,,the most advanced weaponry, okay?\N{\rChinese}最先进的武器，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.12,0:14:24.66,English,,0,0,0,,That's just technology. Propaganda means\N{\rChinese}这只是技术。宣传就是…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.66,0:14:27.10,English,,0,0,0,,that America controls information space.\N{\rChinese}美国掌控信息空间。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.10,0:14:29.08,English,,0,0,0,,It controls the internet.\N{\rChinese}它掌控互联网。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:32.56,English,,0,0,0,,It controls the world's most powerful media,\N{\rChinese}它掌控全球最强大的媒体，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.68,0:14:35.08,English,,0,0,0,,including the New York Times, CNN,\N{\rChinese}包括《纽约时报》、CNN、
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.52,0:14:39.18,English,,0,0,0,,BBC. It controls YouTube.\N{\rChinese}BBC。它掌控YouTube。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.32,0:14:41.90,English,,0,0,0,,It controls Google. It controls information landscape.\N{\rChinese}它掌控Google。它掌控信息景观。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.28,0:14:44.50,English,,0,0,0,,America does not want you to know something.\N{\rChinese}美国不想让你知道这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.60,0:14:47.82,English,,0,0,0,,It can hide it from you. America can control the discourse.\N{\rChinese}它可以把它隐藏在你面前。美国可以掌控话语。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.06,0:14:49.98,English,,0,0,0,,It can control how you think about the world.\N{\rChinese}它能决定你对世界的看法。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:54.84,English,,0,0,0,,That's propaganda. The last thing is money, okay?\N{\rChinese}那是宣传。最后一件事是钱，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.96,0:14:58.62,English,,0,0,0,,And it's a very simple idea. The United States controls the US dollar,\N{\rChinese}美国掌控美元，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.32,0:15:02.70,English,,0,0,0,,which is the reserve currency of the world. And\N{\rChinese}它是世界的储备货币。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.70,0:15:06.38,English,,0,0,0,,the United States can print as much US\N{\rChinese}美国可以按需印制足够的美元，以赢得这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.38,0:15:09.28,English,,0,0,0,,dollars as it needs in order to win this war.\N{\rChinese}美国可以按需印制足够的美元，以赢得这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.44,0:15:11.80,English,,0,0,0,,It has an infinite money printer.\N{\rChinese}它有一台无限印钞机。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:13.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And then\N{\rChinese}好了？然后呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.84,0:15:17.34,English,,0,0,0,,it can use this money to\N{\rChinese}它可以用这笔钱来
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.34,0:15:20.12,English,,0,0,0,,bribe people to fight this war.\N{\rChinese}贿赂人们去打这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.22,0:15:22.12,English,,0,0,0,,It can pay for mercenaries.\N{\rChinese}它可以支付雇佣兵。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.34,0:15:25.72,English,,0,0,0,,It can bribe ethnic minorities to rebel against the government.\N{\rChinese}它可以贿赂少数民族反叛政府。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.72,0:15:30.20,English,,0,0,0,,It can bribe Iranian officials to betray the government.\N{\rChinese}它可以贿赂伊朗官员背叛政府。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.46,0:15:33.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.02,0:15:37.64,English,,0,0,0,,looking at these three things, you would think that America is invisible.\N{\rChinese}看着这三件事，你会觉得美国无形。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.00,0:15:39.68,English,,0,0,0,,Right? But again,\N{\rChinese}对吧？但再说一次，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.98,0:15:42.98,English,,0,0,0,,we need to think about the law's asymmetry\N{\rChinese}我们还得思考这条法则的非对称性。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.98,0:15:46.98,English,,0,0,0,,and recognize that these advantages are also disadvantages.\N{\rChinese}并且认识到这些优势也是劣势。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.90,0:15:50.68,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So, let's discuss this.\N{\rChinese}好的？那我们来讨论一下。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.32,0:15:53.90,English,,0,0,0,,Technology. Well, you know,\N{\rChinese}技术。嗯，你知道的。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.96,0:15:56.70,English,,0,0,0,,if you have those advanced weaponry, in the world,\N{\rChinese}如果你拥有世界上最先进的武器，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.48,0:15:59.56,English,,0,0,0,,you become lazy,\N{\rChinese}你会变得懒散，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.00,0:16:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,arrogant, and dependent on the technology.\N{\rChinese}自负自傲并依赖技术。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.06,0:16:06.22,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So, the classic example, of course, is our school\N{\rChinese}对吧？那么，经典例子当然是我们的学校。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.22,0:16:09.02,English,,0,0,0,,where you have access to chat GPT.\N{\rChinese}在那里你可以使用 ChatGPT。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.92,0:16:13.74,English,,0,0,0,,Right? And like, you become smarter because you have access to chat GPT.\N{\rChinese}对吧？于是你因为使用ChatGPT 而变得更聪明。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.82,0:16:17.14,English,,0,0,0,,No, you become dumber because you become lazy.\N{\rChinese}不，你会变得更笨，因为你变懒了。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.08,0:16:19.74,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Same with technology.\N{\rChinese}对吧？技术也是一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.24,0:16:23.04,English,,0,0,0,,You would think that with the most advanced weaponry in the world,\N{\rChinese}你会以为世界上最先进的武器而自以为傲。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.58,0:16:24.88,English,,0,0,0,,America would become invincible.\N{\rChinese}美国将变得无敌可战。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:27.08,English,,0,0,0,,But instead, people become,\N{\rChinese}但相反，人民变成了……
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.22,0:16:31.46,English,,0,0,0,,the American military becomes too dependent on the technology.\N{\rChinese}美军对技术的依赖过重。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.86,0:16:34.44,English,,0,0,0,,It becomes too arrogant, too complacent.\N{\rChinese}它变得太自大，太自满。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.38,0:16:38.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It's like, well, you know, if we're in trouble,\N{\rChinese}好了？就像，嗯，你知道，如果我们遇到麻烦，
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.42,0:16:40.42,English,,0,0,0,,then we'll just send in the Air Force.\N{\rChinese}那我们就直接派空军来。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:44.56,English,,0,0,0,,And we'll have enough. Okay? So, it leads to dependency.\N{\rChinese}我们会有足够的。好了？于是就形成了依赖。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.02,0:16:50.80,English,,0,0,0,,And this actually hampers innovation\N{\rChinese}这实际上阻碍了创新
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.80,0:16:53.30,English,,0,0,0,,and resilience in the battlefield.\N{\rChinese}并且在战场上造成了韧性不足。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.88,0:16:56.08,English,,0,0,0,,And this is what you need to win. Okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是你赢得胜利所需的。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.28,0:17:00.78,English,,0,0,0,,You need to be innovative and you need to be resilient on the battlefield.\N{\rChinese}你需要在战场上具备创新与韧性。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:05.46,English,,0,0,0,,But because of technology, you become too lazy\N{\rChinese}但因技术，便会变得懒散。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.38,0:17:09.34,English,,0,0,0,,to think for yourself. All right?\N{\rChinese}自己思考。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.50,0:17:11.78,English,,0,0,0,,So, that's one problem. Propaganda.\N{\rChinese}所以，这就是一个问题。宣传。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.88,0:17:15.28,English,,0,0,0,,You would think that, oh, America controls the debate.\N{\rChinese}你会想，哦，美国掌控了辩论。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.74,0:17:17.56,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore, that's a huge advantage.\N{\rChinese}因此，这就是一个巨大的优势。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.86,0:17:19.50,English,,0,0,0,,It's actually not an advantage,\N{\rChinese}其实这并不是优势，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.98,0:17:23.60,English,,0,0,0,,guys. The reason why is that, in order for innovation\N{\rChinese}伙计们。原因在于，为了创新
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.60,0:17:27.50,English,,0,0,0,,and resilience to happen, you need to have open debate.\N{\rChinese}并且韧性得以发生，你需要有开放的辩论。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.64,0:17:33.36,English,,0,0,0,,Right? You need people to voice dissenting opinions.\N{\rChinese}对吧？你需要人们发声异议。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.66,0:17:36.18,English,,0,0,0,,But if you control the information landscape,\N{\rChinese}但若你掌控信息景观，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.62,0:17:38.82,English,,0,0,0,,what you can do is censor.\N{\rChinese}你可以做的就是进行审查。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.44,0:17:41.20,English,,0,0,0,,And that's what America's doing right now.\N{\rChinese}这正是美国现在正在做的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.40,0:17:42.94,English,,0,0,0,,It's telling people to shut up and obey.\N{\rChinese}它让人们闭嘴服从。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.78,0:17:47.02,English,,0,0,0,,You're not allowed to point out that this war is stupid\N{\rChinese}你们不能说这场战争是愚蠢的，美国也赢不了这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.02,0:17:48.88,English,,0,0,0,,and America can't win this war.\N{\rChinese}否则就会被踢出去。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.10,0:17:50.66,English,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you'll be kicked out.\N{\rChinese}Otherwise, you'll be kicked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.78,0:17:53.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:55.96,English,,0,0,0,,this means that\N{\rChinese}这意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.96,0:18:00.52,English,,0,0,0,,there's really a lack of rigorous debate within the American government,\N{\rChinese}美国政府内部确实缺乏严谨的辩论。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.18,0:18:03.52,English,,0,0,0,,within the American military, within the American elite,\N{\rChinese}在美国军队内部，在美国精英内部，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:06.62,English,,0,0,0,,which, of course, will lead to hubris.\N{\rChinese}这当然会导致自负。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.78,0:18:08.68,English,,0,0,0,,It will lead to bad decision making.\N{\rChinese}这将导致决策失误。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.02,0:18:12.68,English,,0,0,0,,No one will point this out because they're too afraid of pissing off\N{\rChinese}没人会指出这一点，因为他们怕惹到总统和他的团队。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.24,0:18:15.06,English,,0,0,0,,the president and his people.\N{\rChinese}于是他们闭嘴，结果美国又一次又一次犯同样的错。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.24,0:18:19.56,English,,0,0,0,,So, they'll shut up and America will keep on making the same mistakes over and over again.\N{\rChinese}So, they'll shut up and America will keep onmaking the same mistakes over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.74,0:18:23.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? We call this the Okay?\N{\rChinese}好的？我们把它叫做“好的”？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.98,0:18:31.70,English,,0,0,0,,They're basically getting high on their own supply is another phrase that we use.\N{\rChinese}他们基本上是靠自己的供应高兴，另外一句我们也用来形容。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.36,0:18:34.84,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Money and wealth.\N{\rChinese}好的。钱和财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.16,0:18:37.58,English,,0,0,0,,You think, okay, well, this is it, man.\N{\rChinese}你想，好的，嗯，就是这样，兄弟。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.82,0:18:41.16,English,,0,0,0,,We just bribe everyone. We just bribe the entire world and\N{\rChinese}我们只要贿赂所有人。我们只要贿赂全世界，然后就好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.16,0:18:43.58,English,,0,0,0,,we're good.\N{\rChinese}我们就好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.74,0:18:45.58,English,,0,0,0,,Right? The problem is this.\N{\rChinese}对吧？问题在于。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.76,0:18:49.60,English,,0,0,0,,The problem is that if you bribe people,\N{\rChinese}问题是如果你贿赂人，
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.14,0:18:52.66,English,,0,0,0,,they're not going to fight for you. Right?\N{\rChinese}他们就不会为你而战。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.96,0:18:54.98,English,,0,0,0,,Because all they want is your money.\N{\rChinese}因为他们只想要你的钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.16,0:18:59.18,English,,0,0,0,,So, you bribe them, but they'll probably take your money and run away.\N{\rChinese}于是你贿赂他们，但他们很可能把钱拿走后逃跑。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:04.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Or they'll figure out how to get more money out of you by cheating you.\N{\rChinese}或者他们会想办法再骗你取更多钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.12,0:19:09.98,English,,0,0,0,,So, right now, the Americans are going to fund these militias\N{\rChinese}于是，现在美国要资助这些民兵、少数民族和反对手对伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.98,0:19:12.92,English,,0,0,0,,and ethnic minorities and opposition groups against Iran.\N{\rChinese}好吗？猜猜看，伙计们？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.12,0:19:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Guess what, guys?\N{\rChinese}Okay? Guess what, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.70,0:19:17.08,English,,0,0,0,,These guys are hustlers. Right?\N{\rChinese}这些人是个贼人。对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.22,0:19:21.60,English,,0,0,0,,They're not fighting because they want more freedom.\N{\rChinese}他们不是为了自由而战斗。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.60,0:19:24.10,English,,0,0,0,,They're fighting because they want to rip off the US government.\N{\rChinese}他们战斗是为了抢美国政府的钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.38,0:19:31.86,English,,0,0,0,,And so, this money issue can be a problem in the long term\N{\rChinese}于是，这笔钱的问题在长期里可能会出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.86,0:19:34.62,English,,0,0,0,,because the people you're bribing, you can't even trust.\N{\rChinese}因为你要贿赂的人，你根本就不可信。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.14,0:19:37.78,English,,0,0,0,,And they're not motivated to actually win this war for you.\N{\rChinese}他们也并非为了帮你赢得这场战争而努力。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.90,0:19:40.60,English,,0,0,0,,They're actually motivated to scam you as much as possible.\N{\rChinese}他们实际上会尽可能多地骗你。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.88,0:19:43.92,English,,0,0,0,,And they could be actually a problem in the long term because\N{\rChinese}而且这在长期里可能成为问题，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.92,0:19:47.14,English,,0,0,0,,you're putting so much resources into these hustlers.\N{\rChinese}你把这么多资源投入到这些贼人身上。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.38,0:19:49.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right.\N{\rChinese}好的？没问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.20,0:19:54.14,English,,0,0,0,,So, what this means is\N{\rChinese}所以，这意味着是
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.14,0:19:59.20,English,,0,0,0,,that America has three major problems.\N{\rChinese}美国有三个主要问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.70,0:20:02.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It has three major problems.\N{\rChinese}好的？它有三个主要问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.32,0:20:09.02,English,,0,0,0,,The first major problem is the lack of political will.\N{\rChinese}第一个主要问题是政治意愿的缺乏。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:15.46,English,,0,0,0,,And all this is saying is that\N{\rChinese}而这一切都说明的是
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.46,0:20:18.98,English,,0,0,0,,the American people don't want to fight this war.\N{\rChinese}美国人民不想打这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:23.68,English,,0,0,0,,The American government, doesn't even know why they're fighting this war.\N{\rChinese}美国政府甚至不知道自己为什么打这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.38,0:20:26.80,English,,0,0,0,,No one cares. Okay?\N{\rChinese}谁也不在乎。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.82,0:20:29.16,English,,0,0,0,,But for the Iranians,\N{\rChinese}但对伊朗人来说，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.70,0:20:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,it's a struggle of life and death.\N{\rChinese}这是一场生死之争。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.84,0:20:36.96,English,,0,0,0,,Right? If America loses this war, they just go home and forget about it.\N{\rChinese}对吧？如果美国赢了这场战争，他们就回家忘了它。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.20,0:20:39.98,English,,0,0,0,,But if the Iranians lose this war, they all get killed.\N{\rChinese}但若伊朗人输掉这场战争，他们就全被杀死。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.20,0:20:43.86,English,,0,0,0,,Or they lose their country, they lose their society, they lose their civilization,\N{\rChinese}或者他们失去国家、社会、文明，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.30,0:20:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,they lose their identity. They cannot afford to lose this war.\N{\rChinese}失去身份。他们不能再输这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.02,0:20:50.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, the first major problem that Americans are facing is,\N{\rChinese}好的？那么，美国人面临的第一个主要问题是，
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.36,0:20:54.58,English,,0,0,0,,they don't have any political will to fight this war, but they're still fighting this war anyway.\N{\rChinese}他们没有任何政治意愿去打这场战争，但仍然在打。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.38,0:20:57.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The question then, of course, is why?\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是问题自然是，为什么会这样？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.80,0:21:02.16,English,,0,0,0,,Why is this happening? This is actually the most important question, and it's the most complicated.\N{\rChinese}为什么会这样？这才是最重要的问题，也是最复杂的。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:04.36,English,,0,0,0,,So, we'll save this for later.\N{\rChinese}所以，我们先留到后面来。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.46,0:21:09.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Second is the idea of logistics\N{\rChinese}好吧？第二个是后勤的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.06,0:21:10.84,English,,0,0,0,,and manufacturing.\N{\rChinese}和制造。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.56,0:21:17.94,English,,0,0,0,,So, America is very good at fighting short wars.\N{\rChinese}所以，美国在短期战争中非常擅长。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.20,0:21:21.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The reason why is, they're advanced,\N{\rChinese}好吧？原因是它们很先进，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.18,0:21:24.92,English,,0,0,0,,they have the most advanced weaponry, but they have manufacturing issues.\N{\rChinese}他们拥有最先进的武器，但制造方面有问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.14,0:21:26.70,English,,0,0,0,,Because, as we know,\N{\rChinese}因为，正如我们所知，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.00,0:21:30.04,English,,0,0,0,,America ships all its factories to China.\N{\rChinese}美国把所有工厂运往中国。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.74,0:21:32.40,English,,0,0,0,,So, America doesn't have that many factories.\N{\rChinese}所以，美国没有那么多的工厂。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.12,0:21:36.28,English,,0,0,0,,So, yes, it has the most advanced weaponry in the world, but\N{\rChinese}所以，是的，它拥有世界上最先进的武器，但……
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.28,0:21:39.38,English,,0,0,0,,this weapon doesn't do any good if you don't have any munitions.\N{\rChinese}如果没有弹药，这种武器也没什么用。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.46,0:21:42.70,English,,0,0,0,,Right? If you don't have any munitions, bombs, bullets.\N{\rChinese}对吧？如果没有弹药、炸弹、子弹。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.08,0:21:44.54,English,,0,0,0,,And you need factories for that.\N{\rChinese}你需要工厂来生产。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.80,0:21:47.50,English,,0,0,0,,America doesn't really have these factories.\N{\rChinese}美国确实没有这些工厂。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.64,0:21:51.97,English,,0,0,0,,Now, I understand that America is trying to\N{\rChinese}现在，我明白美国正试图提升其制造能力，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.10,0:21:54.76,English,,0,0,0,,upgrade its manufacturing capacity,\N{\rChinese}但进展有点慢。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.82,0:21:57.46,English,,0,0,0,,but it's kind of slow.\N{\rChinese}but it's kind ofslow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.44,0:22:02.46,English,,0,0,0,,So maybe five years from now, it will have manufacturing capacity to fight this war,\N{\rChinese}也许在五年后，它将拥有足够的制造能力来打这场战争，但现在还没有。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.58,0:22:04.34,English,,0,0,0,,but right now it doesn't. So\N{\rChinese}这又是另一个主要问题，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.34,0:22:08.34,English,,0,0,0,,that's another major issue, okay?\N{\rChinese}that's another major issue, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.64,0:22:13.22,English,,0,0,0,,And then the last issue, of course, is casualties.\N{\rChinese}然后最后一个问题，当然是伤亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.22,0:22:16.96,English,,0,0,0,,Specialties. All right,\N{\rChinese}专业化。好了，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.00,0:22:20.68,English,,0,0,0,,America, because it doesn't have the political will to fight this war,\N{\rChinese}美国，因为它没有政治意愿去打这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.90,0:22:24.62,English,,0,0,0,,cannot afford to lose soldiers on the battlefield.\N{\rChinese}不能在战场上失去士兵。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.18,0:22:29.42,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So\N{\rChinese}好了？所以
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.42,0:22:32.14,English,,0,0,0,,it wants to minimize the death,\N{\rChinese}它想减少死亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.46,0:22:35.42,English,,0,0,0,,it wants to minimize battlefield losses, because\N{\rChinese}它想在战场上减少损失，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.42,0:22:36.70,English,,0,0,0,,if like a thousand,\N{\rChinese}如果像一千人，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.94,0:22:41.14,English,,0,0,0,,tens of thousands of American soldiers are going home to America dead in coffins,\N{\rChinese}数万美军士兵回国时装在棺材里
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.28,0:22:42.50,English,,0,0,0,,I guarantee you,\N{\rChinese}我向你保证，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.22,0:22:46.06,English,,0,0,0,,because of lack of political will, the American people will revolt.\N{\rChinese}因为缺乏政治意志，美国人民会起义。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:51.62,English,,0,0,0,,You have protests, you will have a lot of violence in the streets.\N{\rChinese}你会有示威，街头会有大乱。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.70,0:22:53.90,English,,0,0,0,,It'll be like the Vietnam era again.\N{\rChinese}就像越战时期一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.72,0:22:57.08,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Okay, so,\N{\rChinese}好的？那好，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.46,0:23:01.68,English,,0,0,0,,yes, I understand that America has technology, propaganda,\N{\rChinese}是的，我知道美国有技术、宣传，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.82,0:23:06.06,English,,0,0,0,,and money, but as we discussed, these aren't really advantages.\N{\rChinese}和钱，但正如我们讨论的那样，这些并不是真正的优势。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.52,0:23:09.04,English,,0,0,0,,And these disadvantages are huge.\N{\rChinese}这些劣势则非常巨大。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.28,0:23:11.20,English,,0,0,0,,The lack of political will, the lack of manufacturing,\N{\rChinese}缺乏政治意志，缺乏制造力。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.86,0:23:15.60,English,,0,0,0,,and the lack of,\N{\rChinese}和缺乏，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.18,0:23:21.94,English,,0,0,0,,America cannot afford to lose that many soldiers in the battlefield, okay? And so,\N{\rChinese}美国不能在战场上失去那么多士兵，好的？于是，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.98,0:23:27.94,English,,0,0,0,,this situation now determines how America will fight this war.\N{\rChinese}此情形现在决定美国将如何作战。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.10,0:23:29.54,English,,0,0,0,,And we'll discuss this later on, okay?\N{\rChinese}好的，稍后再讨论。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.90,0:23:31.48,English,,0,0,0,,All right, now let's talk about Iran.\N{\rChinese}好的，现在来聊聊伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.28,0:23:43.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so, the United States is a very, very, very, very, very, very,\N{\rChinese}好的，接着说，美国是个非常非常非常非常非常非常…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.20,0:23:50.26,English,,0,0,0,,very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very,\N{\rChinese}非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.26,0:23:54.52,English,,0,0,0,,very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very,\N{\rChinese}非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.90,0:23:57.18,English,,0,0,0,,very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very, very,\N{\rChinese}非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，非常，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.38,0:24:01.86,English,,0,0,0,,very, very,\N{\rChinese}非常，非常，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.86,0:24:09.86,English,,0,0,0,,very, of\N{\rChinese}非常，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.86,0:24:15.46,English,,0,0,0,,eschatology, of individual sacrifice for the greater good.\N{\rChinese}末世论，个人牺牲为大义。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.22,0:24:19.00,English,,0,0,0,,The Shia are not afraid to die.\N{\rChinese}什叶派不怕死。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.42,0:24:21.94,English,,0,0,0,,And because their great religious leader,\N{\rChinese}并且因为他们伟大的宗教领袖，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.20,0:24:26.90,English,,0,0,0,,the Ayatollah Khomeini was assassinated by the Americans and Israelis,\N{\rChinese}阿亚图拉·霍梅尼被美以色两国暗杀。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.26,0:24:30.62,English,,0,0,0,,they are motivated to seek vengeance,\N{\rChinese}他们有寻仇的动机
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.44,0:24:33.90,English,,0,0,0,,to martyr themselves for the greater good,\N{\rChinese}为更大善牺牲自己
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.08,0:24:37.54,English,,0,0,0,,to seek eternal paradise, okay, jihad.\N{\rChinese}去寻永生之乐，好的，圣战。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.04,0:24:44.50,English,,0,0,0,,All right, that's the first major advantage.\N{\rChinese}好的，这就是第一个主要优势。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.70,0:24:46.84,English,,0,0,0,,The second major advantage is terrain.\N{\rChinese}第二个主要优势是地形。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.42,0:24:51.20,English,,0,0,0,,And all this means is that\N{\rChinese}而这一切都意味着是……
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.20,0:24:57.10,English,,0,0,0,,Iran is a mountainous country.\N{\rChinese}伊朗是个山地国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.22,0:25:00.76,English,,0,0,0,,And it's huge, it's three times the size of Iraq.\N{\rChinese}它又很大，面积是伊拉克的三倍。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.16,0:25:07.34,English,,0,0,0,,So it's very hard for America to invade the country.\N{\rChinese}因此美国入侵伊朗非常困难。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.90,0:25:11.00,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, most analysts will say,\N{\rChinese}事实上，大多数分析师会说，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.18,0:25:17.06,English,,0,0,0,,will tell you, it is suicidal for the American military to invade Iran.\N{\rChinese}会告诉你，入侵伊朗对美军来说是自杀的事，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.18,0:25:19.40,English,,0,0,0,,It is a mountain fortress, okay, it's a fortress.\N{\rChinese}它是山地堡垒，好的，就是堡垒。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.84,0:25:26.98,English,,0,0,0,,And the last issue is,\N{\rChinese}还有最后一个问题，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.38,0:25:28.84,English,,0,0,0,,the last advantage is nationalism.\N{\rChinese}最后一个优势是民族主义。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.58,0:25:33.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. All right.\N{\rChinese}好的，全部完成。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.36,0:25:37.48,English,,0,0,0,,So the Iranians are Persians.\N{\rChinese}伊朗人是波斯人。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.52,0:25:42.78,English,,0,0,0,,And the Persians go back 5,000 years.\N{\rChinese}波斯人有五千年的历史。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.02,0:25:47.08,English,,0,0,0,,It is one of the greatest civilizations in human history.\N{\rChinese}它是人类历史上最伟大的文明之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.32,0:25:51.30,English,,0,0,0,,And as we discussed last semester, in the ancient world, there were three great civilizations,\N{\rChinese}正如上学期所说，古代有三大文明，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.68,0:25:54.32,English,,0,0,0,,right, the Jews, the Greeks, and the Persians.\N{\rChinese}对，犹太人、希腊人和波斯人。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.60,0:25:59.56,English,,0,0,0,,And the Persian culture, it's vast, it's beautiful,\N{\rChinese}波斯文化广阔而美丽。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.16,0:26:02.24,English,,0,0,0,,and it's deep, and\N{\rChinese}并且很深厚，且
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.24,0:26:05.70,English,,0,0,0,,that's what gives the Iranian people a lot of pride,\N{\rChinese}这就是伊朗人自豪的原因，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.92,0:26:09.48,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So, when they're fighting,\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以他们打仗时，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.62,0:26:13.06,English,,0,0,0,,they're not just fighting for their religion, they're not just fighting for their homes,\N{\rChinese}他们不只是为宗教而战，也不只是为家园而战，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.18,0:26:14.98,English,,0,0,0,,they're fighting for their entire civilization\N{\rChinese}他们为整个文明而战
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.48,0:26:16.86,English,,0,0,0,,that goes back 5,000 years.\N{\rChinese}这文明可追溯五千年前
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.58,0:26:20.36,English,,0,0,0,,Right, so these are the three major advantages\N{\rChinese}好的，下面是伊朗人拥有的三大优势
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.50,0:26:24.06,English,,0,0,0,,that the Iranians have, okay?\N{\rChinese}那就是伊朗人的三大优势，明白了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.12,0:26:27.12,English,,0,0,0,,Faith means that they're not afraid to die\N{\rChinese}信仰意味着他们不怕牺
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.98,0:26:29.60,English,,0,0,0,,for what they believe in.\N{\rChinese}为他们所信仰的事物。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.14,0:26:33.96,English,,0,0,0,,Terrain means that the Americans will have a hard problem invading the country.\N{\rChinese}地形意味着美国人入侵该国时会遇到大难。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.14,0:26:39.94,English,,0,0,0,,Nationalism means that the people will be able to live, they will all be reigned, know what they're fighting for.\N{\rChinese}民族主义让人民能自足，统一，明白自己在为之而战。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.84,0:26:44.02,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? So, but again, remember,\N{\rChinese}好的？那好，记住，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.24,0:26:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,everything that seems like an advantage can be a disadvantage as well, alright?\N{\rChinese}所有看似优势的事也可能是劣势，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.92,0:26:53.24,English,,0,0,0,,So, let's go over what the problems are.\N{\rChinese}好了，先说说问题在哪。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.48,0:26:57.56,English,,0,0,0,,With faith, you might have an issue of blindness,\N{\rChinese}凭信念，你可能会出现盲目之症，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.92,0:27:00.28,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Or zealotry.\N{\rChinese}好吗？或者是狂热。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.00,0:27:05.68,English,,0,0,0,,Where you're not afraid to die,\N{\rChinese}你不怕死的那一刻。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.58,0:27:09.14,English,,0,0,0,,but that means that\N{\rChinese}但那就意味着……
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.14,0:27:11.42,English,,0,0,0,,you're not thinking strategically, okay?\N{\rChinese}你没有在思考战略，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.22,0:27:15.14,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're gonna waste too many soldiers on the battlefield.\N{\rChinese}你可能会在战场上浪费太多兵力。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.62,0:27:17.96,English,,0,0,0,,They're brave, but they're kind of stupid as well.\N{\rChinese}他们很勇敢，但也有点傻气。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.48,0:27:20.78,English,,0,0,0,,Alright, so you might have an issue\N{\rChinese}好了，可能会出现……
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.88,0:27:26.08,English,,0,0,0,,where Iran is not using the optimal strategy\N{\rChinese}伊朗没有采用最优策略。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.60,0:27:30.44,English,,0,0,0,,because their soldiers are not afraid of death.\N{\rChinese}因为他们的士兵不怕死亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.76,0:27:32.96,English,,0,0,0,,And we're already seeing that where\N{\rChinese}而我们已经看到的情况是……
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.96,0:27:36.40,English,,0,0,0,,the Americans have already blown up and destroyed the Iranian navy.\N{\rChinese}美国已经炸毁并摧毁了伊朗海军。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.84,0:27:39.22,English,,0,0,0,,Now, any of you guys know that, right? I'm not saying that you're not afraid,\N{\rChinese}现在，你们中有人知道这件事吧？我不是说你们不怕，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.22,0:27:42.36,English,,0,0,0,,the first thing the Americans would do is go destroy the Iranian navy,\N{\rChinese}美国首先会去摧毁伊朗海军，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.56,0:27:47.30,English,,0,0,0,,so you should probably not use the navy, or hide the navy, or blow up the navy yourself,\N{\rChinese}所以你们最好不要用海军，或者把海军隐藏起来，或者自己炸掉海军。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.68,0:27:50.40,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Because you want to avoid as many casualties as possible,\N{\rChinese}好的？因为你想尽量避免伤亡，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.04,0:27:55.14,English,,0,0,0,,but they didn't do that, and the Americans have now destroyed the Iranian navy,\N{\rChinese}但他们没这么做，结果美国又摧毁了伊朗海军，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.32,0:27:57.56,English,,0,0,0,,alright? So, that's the issue of faith.\N{\rChinese}好了？这就是信念的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.80,0:28:00.68,English,,0,0,0,,Terrain, yeah, it's a fortress,\N{\rChinese}地形，嗯，是一座堡垒，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.04,0:28:04.08,English,,0,0,0,,but it can also be a prison, right?\N{\rChinese}它也可以是个牢房，没错吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.88,0:28:07.50,English,,0,0,0,,Where you're just sort of stuck there, and because\N{\rChinese}你就那样被卡住了，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.50,0:28:10.44,English,,0,0,0,,it's a mountainous region, it doesn't have that many resources,\N{\rChinese}它是个山地地区，资源不多，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.70,0:28:13.72,English,,0,0,0,,so Americans can actually disrupt your water supply,\N{\rChinese}美国人可以切断你的水源，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.90,0:28:17.60,English,,0,0,0,,disrupt your electricity, okay, and cause general poverty\N{\rChinese}切断电力，造成普遍贫困
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.60,0:28:20.94,English,,0,0,0,,and hardship for your people, okay?\N{\rChinese}和你们人民的艰辛，没错吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.38,0:28:22.92,English,,0,0,0,,And then nationalism,\N{\rChinese}然后是民族主义，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.28,0:28:26.38,English,,0,0,0,,yes, Persia is a great culture, but\N{\rChinese}是的，波斯是伟大的文化，但
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.38,0:28:32.18,English,,0,0,0,,remember that Iran is an ethnically diverse country.\N{\rChinese}记住伊朗是个民族多样的国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.40,0:28:37.52,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, only 50% of the population of Iran in the Terrain are Persians.\N{\rChinese}实际上，伊朗人口中只有50%是波斯人。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.90,0:28:40.86,English,,0,0,0,,Others are different minorities, okay?\N{\rChinese}其余者是各类少数民族，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.42,0:28:44.58,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? So, you have\N{\rChinese}好的？那么，你有…
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.58,0:28:48.80,English,,0,0,0,,then ethnic divisions, right?\N{\rChinese}然后是民族分裂，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.50,0:28:54.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, looking at this,\N{\rChinese}好的？看着这个…
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.34,0:28:59.76,English,,0,0,0,,now we know exactly what the American strategy will be.\N{\rChinese}现在我们已经完全知道美国的战略是什么了。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.00,0:29:01.76,English,,0,0,0,,Basically, the strategy will be\N{\rChinese}基本上，这个战略就是……
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.76,0:29:08.20,English,,0,0,0,,to inflict as many casualties as possible on the Iranians,\N{\rChinese}对伊朗人造成尽可能多的伤亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.28,0:29:09.48,English,,0,0,0,,alright?\N{\rChinese}好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.58,0:29:14.70,English,,0,0,0,,To kill as many people as possible, destroy the infrastructure of Iran\N{\rChinese}杀尽可能多的人，摧毁伊朗的基础设施，令人民缺水缺电缺粮，才能生存，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.70,0:29:19.36,English,,0,0,0,,so that the people don't have enough water, electricity, food to survive, okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.70,0:29:20.68,English,,0,0,0,,And the third, of course,\N{\rChinese}第三点当然是
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.92,0:29:26.10,English,,0,0,0,,is to create as much ethnic tension in the country as possible by arming\N{\rChinese}在国内通过武装和鼓动来制造尽可能多的民族紧张。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.10,0:29:27.40,English,,0,0,0,,and encouraging and\N{\rChinese}and encouragingand
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.40,0:29:32.00,English,,0,0,0,,bribing ethnic groups to rebel against the central government in Terrain,\N{\rChinese}给各族群贿赂，让他们在领土上反叛中央政府
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.18,0:29:34.60,English,,0,0,0,,alright? Okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.60,0:29:36.22,English,,0,0,0,,But again,\N{\rChinese}再说一次，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.76,0:29:41.46,English,,0,0,0,,what the law of symmetry, asymmetry tells us is\N{\rChinese}什么是对称律与非对称律告诉我们的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.46,0:29:45.62,English,,0,0,0,,that the empire ultimately is not as flexible\N{\rChinese}帝国最终并不像其敌人那样灵活
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.62,0:29:49.58,English,,0,0,0,,and open and dynamic as its enemy,\N{\rChinese}并且开放且动态
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.82,0:29:50.76,English,,0,0,0,,okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.42,0:29:56.20,English,,0,0,0,,The weaker person is going to engage in much more self -reflection,\N{\rChinese}弱者将会进行更多的自省思考，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.46,0:30:01.48,English,,0,0,0,,self -debate than the empire,\N{\rChinese}自我辩论
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.76,0:30:03.60,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Because the empire will become arrogant.\N{\rChinese}好吧？因为帝国会变得自负。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.60,0:30:04.82,English,,0,0,0,,And so ultimately,\N{\rChinese}于是，最终，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.28,0:30:09.86,English,,0,0,0,,Iran should triumph over America.\N{\rChinese}伊朗应当战胜美国。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.24,0:30:13.20,English,,0,0,0,,And in fact, what's going to happen is that\N{\rChinese}而且，实际上会发生的事是
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.20,0:30:16.82,English,,0,0,0,,this strategy that America will use\N{\rChinese}美国将会使用的这套策略
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.60,0:30:23.52,English,,0,0,0,,against the Iranians will lead to the Iranians becoming much more energetic,\N{\rChinese}对伊朗人来说会使他们更为活跃
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.60,0:30:26.26,English,,0,0,0,,open, and cohesive,\N{\rChinese}打开，并连贯，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.72,0:30:27.96,English,,0,0,0,,okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.30,0:30:31.88,English,,0,0,0,,So, let's look at the American strategy specifically.\N{\rChinese}于是，让我们具体看看美国的策略。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.88,0:30:41.50,English,,0,0,0,,And, anyway, we're gonna deal with that shortly.\N{\rChinese}好吧，我们很快会处理这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.50,0:30:45.12,English,,0,0,0,,we're gonna deal with that shortly. And, anyway, we're gonna deal with that shortly.\N{\rChinese}我们很快会处理这个。好吧，我们很快会处理这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.80,0:30:48.06,English,,0,0,0,,And, anyway, And, anyway, we're gonna deal with that shortly.\N{\rChinese}好吧，好吧，我们很快会处理这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.20,0:30:51.08,English,,0,0,0,,And, anyway, we're gonna deal with that shortly. And, anyway, And, anyway, we're gonna deal with that shortly.\N{\rChinese}好吧，我们很快会处理这个。好吧，好吧，我们很快会处理这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.74,0:30:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,And, anyway, we're gonna deal with that shortly.\N{\rChinese}好吧，我们很快会处理这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.64,0:30:56.56,English,,0,0,0,,And, anyway, we're gonna deal with that shortly.\N{\rChinese}好吧，我们很快会处理这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.40,0:30:59.76,English,,0,0,0,,And, anyway, we're gonna deal with that shortly.\N{\rChinese}好吧，反正，咱们很快会处理这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.28,0:31:01.60,English,,0,0,0,,And, anyway,\N{\rChinese}好吧，反正，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.58,0:31:05.10,English,,0,0,0,,and the Baliks.\N{\rChinese}以及巴利克人。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.39,0:31:10.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? These are the three major problem areas for Iran,\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是伊朗的三大问题区。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.10,0:31:12.48,English,,0,0,0,,and it's always been the case.\N{\rChinese}而且这一直是事实。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.62,0:31:15.06,English,,0,0,0,,Remember, the Persians are in the middle.\N{\rChinese}记住，波斯人处于中间。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.36,0:31:18.86,English,,0,0,0,,So, the Baliks are, first of all,\N{\rChinese}于是，巴利克人首先是，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.90,0:31:20.40,English,,0,0,0,,Sunni Muslims.\N{\rChinese}逊尼穆斯林。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.56,0:31:24.48,English,,0,0,0,,As we discussed last class, the Sunnis and\N{\rChinese}正如上节所说，逊尼人和
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.48,0:31:27.20,English,,0,0,0,,the Shias have never really gotten along well together.\N{\rChinese}什叶派从来就不太能和睦邻相处。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.56,0:31:31.00,English,,0,0,0,,They have different, I mean, the same religion, Islam,\N{\rChinese}他们有同宗教，伊斯兰，差别在信仰体系。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.16,0:31:32.38,English,,0,0,0,,but they have different belief systems.\N{\rChinese}但信仰体系各不相同。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.38,0:31:35.38,English,,0,0,0,,That's led to a lot of conflicts in the past.\N{\rChinese}这导致了过去的许多冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.62,0:31:37.40,English,,0,0,0,,It's almost like the Catholics and the Protestants, okay?\N{\rChinese}就像天主教和新教一样，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.74,0:31:43.06,English,,0,0,0,,And so, the Baliks have been trying to rebel against Iranians for a long time.\N{\rChinese}于是，巴利克人长期试图反抗伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.14,0:31:46.20,English,,0,0,0,,I guarantee you that there are already Israeli\N{\rChinese}我向你保证，已经有以色列人和美军特种部队驻扎在此地，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.20,0:31:49.44,English,,0,0,0,,and American special forces embedded in this area, okay?\N{\rChinese}原因是……
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.56,0:31:51.40,English,,0,0,0,,The reason why is that\N{\rChinese}The reason why is that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.40,0:31:55.38,English,,0,0,0,,they want to encourage as much civil conflict as possible,\N{\rChinese}他们想尽可能多地制造内战，但也想为地面入侵美国做准备。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.58,0:32:00.78,English,,0,0,0,,but they also want to prepare the possibility for a ground invasion of America.\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以，】
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.32,0:32:03.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}Okay? So,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.36,0:32:07.94,English,,0,0,0,,they would need a forward operating base, and\N{\rChinese}他们需要一个前进作战基地，而这片地区可以成为陆权入侵的起点。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.94,0:32:13.26,English,,0,0,0,,this area could be a very good place for a beginning of a land invasion.\N{\rChinese}然后你来到这里，你会遇到库尔德人。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.98,0:32:16.08,English,,0,0,0,,Then you over here, you have the Kurds.\N{\rChinese}Then you over here,you have the Kurds.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.30,0:32:19.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Kurds are another minority that\N{\rChinese}好的？库尔德人是另一支寻求民族主权的少数民族。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.56,0:32:21.16,English,,0,0,0,,seeks national sovereignty.\N{\rChinese}现在，正在发生的事是…
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.84,0:32:25.80,English,,0,0,0,,And right now, what's happening is\N{\rChinese}And right now, what's happening is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.80,0:32:29.68,English,,0,0,0,,that the Americans and Israelis are bombing this area heavily,\N{\rChinese}美国和以色列人正在猛烈轰炸这片地区，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.84,0:32:32.18,English,,0,0,0,,and they're targeting police stations.\N{\rChinese}他们正瞄准警察局。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.38,0:32:35.56,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because they're trying to reduce and\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为他们想要减少…
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.56,0:32:38.36,English,,0,0,0,,eliminate opposition so that\N{\rChinese}消除对手，以便
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.36,0:32:41.82,English,,0,0,0,,they can arm the Kurds and have them come into this area\N{\rChinese}他们可以给库尔德人武装，让他们进入此区
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.82,0:32:45.00,English,,0,0,0,,and threaten Iran.\N{\rChinese}并威胁伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.10,0:32:47.70,English,,0,0,0,,What's also happening is that in Iraq,\N{\rChinese}在伊拉克也在发生同样的事，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.86,0:32:53.80,English,,0,0,0,,there are these Sunni groups,\N{\rChinese}有这些逊尼团体，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.06,0:32:58.34,English,,0,0,0,,okay, that the Americans are basically bribing\N{\rChinese}美国基本上在贿赐
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.34,0:33:02.28,English,,0,0,0,,and arming, and they're basically fanatics.\N{\rChinese}并且武装，基本是狂热分子。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.38,0:33:04.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They're ISIS. And\N{\rChinese}好？他们是ISIS。还有
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.62,0:33:06.80,English,,0,0,0,,what the Americans want to do is send\N{\rChinese}美国想做的事是派
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.80,0:33:11.26,English,,0,0,0,,them into Iran to cause as much problems as possible.\N{\rChinese}把他们送到伊朗，制造尽可能多的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.66,0:33:14.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Then you over here, you have Azerbaijan.\N{\rChinese}好？然后你在这里，你有阿塞拜疆。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.86,0:33:20.74,English,,0,0,0,,Azerbaijan, it is an independent country.\N{\rChinese}阿塞拜疆，它是一个独立的国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.98,0:33:22.92,English,,0,0,0,,What's really odd is that\N{\rChinese}真正奇怪的是
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.92,0:33:27.58,English,,0,0,0,,the majority of ethnic Azeris are actually in Iran.\N{\rChinese}大多数阿塞拜疆族人实际上在伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.08,0:33:30.86,English,,0,0,0,,Six percent are in the country.\N{\rChinese}六个百分点在阿塞拜疆国。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.96,0:33:32.36,English,,0,0,0,,Forty percent are...\N{\rChinese}四十％在……
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.38,0:33:35.06,English,,0,0,0,,Forty percent are in the country of Azerbaijan, which means that\N{\rChinese}四十％在阿塞拜疆国，这意味着……
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.06,0:33:37.74,English,,0,0,0,,from the perspective of the Azerbaijani people,\N{\rChinese}从阿塞拜疆人的角度来看……
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.26,0:33:41.98,English,,0,0,0,,this war could be an\N{\rChinese}这场战争可能是一个机会，
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.98,0:33:45.36,English,,0,0,0,,opportunity to reunite the people,\N{\rChinese}可以让人们团聚，
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.68,0:33:48.52,English,,0,0,0,,okay, and create a greater Azerbaijan.\N{\rChinese}好，形成更大的阿塞拜疆。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.08,0:33:51.86,English,,0,0,0,,So these are the three problem areas\N{\rChinese}于是这三大问题区间……
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.86,0:33:57.26,English,,0,0,0,,that you have to watch as this war develops over the next few weeks,\N{\rChinese}你需要在接下来几周内跟踪……
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.32,0:33:58.80,English,,0,0,0,,over the next few months. Okay?\N{\rChinese}以及接下来几个月内观察……
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.16,0:34:02.36,English,,0,0,0,,So, we already know what's happening.\N{\rChinese}于是，我们已经知道发生了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.36,0:34:06.12,English,,0,0,0,,We already know what the American strategy will be because we've seen it in Libya,\N{\rChinese}我们已经知道美国的策略是什么，因为我们已经在利比亚看到过。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.42,0:34:08.02,English,,0,0,0,,in Syria before.\N{\rChinese}我们已经知道美国的策略是什么，因为我们已经在叙利亚看到过。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.96,0:34:10.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so what is the strategy?\N{\rChinese}好的，那策略是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.76,0:34:13.20,English,,0,0,0,,Right. So, again,\N{\rChinese}对，回到起点。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.36,0:34:17.78,English,,0,0,0,,the strategy is to both attack without,\N{\rChinese}策略是从外部同时发动攻击，
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.20,0:34:21.22,English,,0,0,0,,okay, from outside, and inside as well.\N{\rChinese}好的，从外部也从内部同时进行。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.78,0:34:23.26,English,,0,0,0,,So, what you're going to do is this.\N{\rChinese}于是，你接下来要做的事就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.40,0:34:26.40,English,,0,0,0,,You're going to arm these people,\N{\rChinese}你要给这些人配备武器。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.60,0:34:31.04,English,,0,0,0,,embed special forces into these insurgent groups to lead them.\N{\rChinese}嵌入特种部队到这些叛军团中，领其作战。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.04,0:34:32.94,English,,0,0,0,,You're going to attack them and provide air cover so\N{\rChinese}你将攻击他们并提供空中掩护。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.94,0:34:37.12,English,,0,0,0,,they have a clear path into Iran and are able to limit opposition, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们有一条清晰的路线进入伊朗，并能限制反对手，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.04,0:34:41.28,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So, now you're attacking from without.\N{\rChinese}好了，现在你从外部发动攻击。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.54,0:34:47.82,English,,0,0,0,,With attacking from within means to cause as much pain\N{\rChinese}从内部发动攻击意味着造成尽可能多的痛苦
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.82,0:34:49.74,English,,0,0,0,,and suffering in the interior\N{\rChinese}以及内部的苦难
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.10,0:34:52.32,English,,0,0,0,,of Iran as possible. All right?\N{\rChinese}伊朗的可能性。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.34,0:34:55.70,English,,0,0,0,,And how do you do that? Well, you do that through decapitation.\N{\rChinese}然后你怎么做？好吧，你通过去头部来做。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.56,0:34:57.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go over the strategies.\N{\rChinese}好了，接下来我们来回顾一下策略。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.30,0:35:01.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Decapitation.\N{\rChinese}好的。去头部。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.58,0:35:05.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. And\N{\rChinese}好的。还有
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.48,0:35:09.32,English,,0,0,0,,what you're doing is you're removing the elite,\N{\rChinese}你正在做的就是去掉精英。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.46,0:35:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,okay, or what we call command and control.\N{\rChinese}好的，或者我们称之为指挥控制。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.24,0:35:22.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You're basically limiting the capacity of Iran to govern itself,\N{\rChinese}好的？你基本上限制了伊朗自我治理的能力，拥有领导层，拥有精英。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.40,0:35:24.82,English,,0,0,0,,to have a leadership, to have an elite. All right?\N{\rChinese}好了，全部就这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.88,0:35:26.98,English,,0,0,0,,Command and control. Okay? So, that's the first strategy.\N{\rChinese}指挥控制。好吧？这就是第一个策略。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.66,0:35:29.76,English,,0,0,0,,Second strategy. Okay.\N{\rChinese}第二个策略。好。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.52,0:35:35.26,English,,0,0,0,,And the third strategy is aerial bombardment, okay?\N{\rChinese}第三个策略是空中轰炸，好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.32,0:35:40.34,English,,0,0,0,,Aerial supremacy. So,\N{\rChinese}空中霸权。于是，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.46,0:35:44.42,English,,0,0,0,,again, America has the most advanced airplanes in the world.\N{\rChinese}再说一次，美国拥有世界上最先进的飞机。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.56,0:35:46.02,English,,0,0,0,,And the way that\N{\rChinese}而且方式是
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.02,0:35:51.80,English,,0,0,0,,it's using its airplanes is to destroy as much military installation as possible,\N{\rChinese}它使用飞机的目的是尽可能摧毁军事设施，
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.00,0:35:56.14,English,,0,0,0,,but it's also engaging in acts of sabotage.\N{\rChinese}它还在进行破坏行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.36,0:35:59.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, what they're doing is they're carpet bombing.\N{\rChinese}他们正在进行地毯轰炸。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.98,0:36:06.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, they're carpet bombing Tehran.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是，他们在对德黑兰进行地毯轰炸。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.30,0:36:11.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They're doing soft targeting.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们在进行软目标打击。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.58,0:36:17.86,English,,0,0,0,,Soft targeting. Soft targeting means that instead of attacking military installations, you attack hospitals.\N{\rChinese}软目标打击是指不是攻击军事设施，而是攻击医院。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.26,0:36:19.54,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.54,0:36:24.22,English,,0,0,0,,you're degrading the capacity to rejuvenate itself,\N{\rChinese}你正在削弱自身的再生能力，
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.34,0:36:28.42,English,,0,0,0,,to be resilient. Okay? Now, the last thing is something called double tap.\N{\rChinese}以便更具韧性。好了？最后一件事叫双击。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.96,0:36:31.22,English,,0,0,0,,Double tap is this. Okay?\N{\rChinese}双击就是这样。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.88,0:36:36.12,English,,0,0,0,,And it's really illegal or against international law.\N{\rChinese}它真的很不合法，或者说是违反国际法的。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.32,0:36:38.30,English,,0,0,0,,What you do is this. You attack a place.\N{\rChinese}你所做的就是这样。你先攻击一个地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.78,0:36:42.00,English,,0,0,0,,Right? You kill some people. And then people try to come\N{\rChinese}对吧？你先杀几个人。然后人们会去赶来救伤者。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.00,0:36:44.24,English,,0,0,0,,and help the people who are injured.\N{\rChinese}他们可能就是医生。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.70,0:36:47.30,English,,0,0,0,,And they could be like doctors.\N{\rChinese}And they could be like doctors.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.60,0:36:49.12,English,,0,0,0,,It could be emergency personnel.\N{\rChinese}它可能是急救人员。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.42,0:36:50.82,English,,0,0,0,,It could be relatives. Right? And then\N{\rChinese}它可能是亲属。对吧？然后
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.82,0:36:54.72,English,,0,0,0,,you strike again to create as many civilian casualties as possible.\N{\rChinese}你再打一次，制造尽可能多的平民伤亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.78,0:36:59.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the entire idea is to create as much fear\N{\rChinese}好的？整个想法就是制造尽可能多的恐惧与焦虑
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.22,0:37:02.52,English,,0,0,0,,and anxiety in people as possible\N{\rChinese}让人们失去抵抗的能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.52,0:37:06.12,English,,0,0,0,,so that they lose the capacity to resist.\N{\rChinese}so that they lose the capacity to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.26,0:37:09.08,English,,0,0,0,,And the last thing you do...\N{\rChinese}然后你做的最后一件事……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.08,0:37:11.88,English,,0,0,0,,And the last thing, of course,\N{\rChinese}最后一件事，当然是……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.00,0:37:15.34,English,,0,0,0,,is to arm\N{\rChinese}就是武装
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.34,0:37:18.78,English,,0,0,0,,and bribe insurgents.\N{\rChinese}并贿赂叛军。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.02,0:37:24.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, these are the three main pillars of the American strategy.\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以，这就是美国战略的三大支柱。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.16,0:37:26.52,English,,0,0,0,,And you will see this over the next few weeks.\N{\rChinese}接下来几周你会看到这一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.18,0:37:31.42,English,,0,0,0,,The problem with this is\N{\rChinese}问题在于……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.42,0:37:33.46,English,,0,0,0,,that when you do these three things,\N{\rChinese}当你做这三件事时，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.70,0:37:36.24,English,,0,0,0,,you're not actually hurting the Iranians.\N{\rChinese}你并没有真正伤害伊朗人。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.34,0:37:38.14,English,,0,0,0,,You're actually helping them.\N{\rChinese}你实际上在帮他们。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.44,0:37:41.42,English,,0,0,0,,Because remember, the law of asymmetry states\N{\rChinese}因为记得，非对称法则说……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.42,0:37:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,that whichever group is able to create energy,\N{\rChinese}……只要哪一方能创造能量，
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.26,0:37:48.20,English,,0,0,0,,openness, and cohesion will win.\N{\rChinese}开放与凝聚将获胜。
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.40,0:37:54.14,English,,0,0,0,,And guess what, guys? This American strategy is going to create a more powerful\N{\rChinese}猜猜怎么了，伙计们？这美国策略将造就更强大的……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.14,0:37:56.62,English,,0,0,0,,and more powerful group. A more energetic, more open, and\N{\rChinese}更有活力、更开放、更有活力的……
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.62,0:37:59.64,English,,0,0,0,,more cohesive Persian society.\N{\rChinese}更具凝聚力的波斯社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.18,0:38:01.52,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Let me show you how.\N{\rChinese}好的？让我来演示。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.98,0:38:03.30,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Decapitation.\N{\rChinese}好的。去头术。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.42,0:38:09.00,English,,0,0,0,,We just said that one major problem for America is elite overproduction.\N{\rChinese}我们刚才说过，美国的一个主要问题是精英过剩。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.28,0:38:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Well, with decapitation,\N{\rChinese}对吧？好吧，去头术之后，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.10,0:38:17.00,English,,0,0,0,,what you're doing is you're\N{\rChinese}你正在做的就是你……
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.00,0:38:19.18,English,,0,0,0,,solving this problem for the Iranians.\N{\rChinese}解决了伊朗人的这个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.54,0:38:24.12,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Before, the huge problem for the Iranians were you have too many leaders, too many leaders And now, you're doing this to the Iranians.\N{\rChinese}之前，伊朗人的大问题是领导层过多，过多，过多。现在，你正在为伊朗人做这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.12,0:38:28.26,English,,0,0,0,,And they all have their own stupid opinion and they all want to lead this war.\N{\rChinese}他们都有自己的傻瓜想法，都想带领这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.40,0:38:30.86,English,,0,0,0,,Right? But by killing so many leaders,\N{\rChinese}对吧？但杀掉这么多领导人，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.14,0:38:35.28,English,,0,0,0,,you allow for more mobility,\N{\rChinese}你就让他们更灵活，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.64,0:38:37.02,English,,0,0,0,,for more meritocracy.\N{\rChinese}更能体现才干的制度。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.32,0:38:41.24,English,,0,0,0,,Right? You're solving the problem of elite overproduction for the Iranians.\N{\rChinese}对吧？你正在解决伊朗人精英过剩的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.50,0:38:43.64,English,,0,0,0,,That's a huge, huge bonus, guys.\N{\rChinese}这可是一个巨大的、巨大的加分，伙计们。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.80,0:38:46.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.52,0:38:49.36,English,,0,0,0,,the leadership will become much more lean,\N{\rChinese}领导层将变得更精简，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.54,0:38:53.72,English,,0,0,0,,much more mean, much more determined, and much more strategic.\N{\rChinese}更有决断力，更有决意，且更具战略性。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.42,0:38:56.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's number one.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是第一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.82,0:38:58.16,English,,0,0,0,,Number two, Arab supremacy.\N{\rChinese}第二点，阿拉伯霸权。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.38,0:39:02.34,English,,0,0,0,,Well, when you do this to people, you cover bomb Tehran,\N{\rChinese}好吧，当你把这件事做给人们时，覆盖德黑兰的炸弹，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.58,0:39:04.64,English,,0,0,0,,you're creating a more cohesive society.\N{\rChinese}你就能创造一个更团结的社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.86,0:39:08.76,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.76,0:39:13.94,English,,0,0,0,,the major conflict in Iran for many decades was the conflict between the urban areas\N{\rChinese}多年来伊朗的主要冲突是城市地区与乡村地区之间的冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.94,0:39:16.86,English,,0,0,0,,and the rural areas. The rural areas were very religious,\N{\rChinese}乡村地区非常宗教化。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.00,0:39:18.82,English,,0,0,0,,very poor, very backward.\N{\rChinese}非常贫穷，十分落后。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.08,0:39:20.92,English,,0,0,0,,And the urban areas were educated,\N{\rChinese}而城市地区则受过教育，世俗化，且…
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.28,0:39:23.34,English,,0,0,0,,secular, and...\N{\rChinese}secular, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.34,0:39:25.16,English,,0,0,0,,Right? They were very progressive. Okay?\N{\rChinese}对吗？他们很进步。好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.30,0:39:29.20,English,,0,0,0,,And so, there's this huge conflict that led to a lot of riots,\N{\rChinese}于是，出现了这场大冲突，导致伊朗发生了大量骚乱，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.26,0:39:31.90,English,,0,0,0,,a lot of protests in Iran.\N{\rChinese}随后出现了大量示威。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.12,0:39:35.00,English,,0,0,0,,But when you cover bomb the cities,\N{\rChinese}但当你轰炸城市时，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.14,0:39:39.88,English,,0,0,0,,which are the main source of support for progressive Western policies,\N{\rChinese}它们是支持进步西方政策的主要来源，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.24,0:39:43.84,English,,0,0,0,,you make them united with the rural areas.\N{\rChinese}你把他们与农村地区团结起来。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.98,0:39:45.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}好了？这样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.98,0:39:48.94,English,,0,0,0,,The Iranian people no longer see themselves, each other, as enemies.\N{\rChinese}伊朗人民不再把彼此视为敌人。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.16,0:39:51.78,English,,0,0,0,,They see the Americans, the Israelis, as enemies.\N{\rChinese}他们把美国人、以色列人视为敌人。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.00,0:39:53.70,English,,0,0,0,,You create a much more cohesive society.\N{\rChinese}你创造了更为凝聚的社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.70,0:39:54.92,English,,0,0,0,,Which are...\N{\rChinese}它们是……
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.92,0:39:57.40,English,,0,0,0,,Who are willing to fight together.\N{\rChinese}谁愿意一起作战
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.76,0:39:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,And that's a problem.\N{\rChinese}这就是问题所在
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.38,0:40:00.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right.\N{\rChinese}好的？没问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.92,0:40:04.74,English,,0,0,0,,The last thing. Yes, you are arming the assertions,\N{\rChinese}最后一件事。是的，你正在装备主张。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.78,0:40:07.04,English,,0,0,0,,the Bullocks, the Kurds, the Israelis.\N{\rChinese}布尔克人、库尔德人、以色列人。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.60,0:40:11.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's fine. The problem with this is\N{\rChinese}好？没问题。这个的难点在于
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.16,0:40:14.46,English,,0,0,0,,that you are now activating,\N{\rChinese}你现在正把它们激活，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.74,0:40:17.52,English,,0,0,0,,galvanizing Persian nationalism.\N{\rChinese}激发波斯民族主义。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.60,0:40:23.68,English,,0,0,0,,Right? For the longest time, you've been doing this.\N{\rChinese}对吗？你已经做了很久。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.68,0:40:29.00,English,,0,0,0,,For the longest time, the Persian national identity was suppressed by the theocracy.\N{\rChinese}在很长一段时间里，波斯民族身份被神权统治压抑。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.36,0:40:31.52,English,,0,0,0,,Because they want to create a more...\N{\rChinese}因为他们想创造一个更…
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.52,0:40:36.12,English,,0,0,0,,They want to create a grand religion that unites all ethnicities.\N{\rChinese}他们想创造一个统一所有民族的伟大宗教。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.46,0:40:41.08,English,,0,0,0,,When you turn the other minorities against the Iranians,\N{\rChinese}当你把其他少数民族拉到伊朗人对立时，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.08,0:40:43.66,English,,0,0,0,,then the Persian people have to come together and\N{\rChinese}然后波斯人要聚在一起，记住自己的历史，庆祝自己的身份。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.66,0:40:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,remember their history, celebrate their identity.\N{\rChinese}这才是关键。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.54,0:40:49.26,English,,0,0,0,,And this is the key. Okay?\N{\rChinese}And this is thekey. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.26,0:40:55.18,English,,0,0,0,,Once the Persian people are able to activate their long -lost memories,\N{\rChinese}一旦波斯人能够激活久失的记忆，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.42,0:40:57.80,English,,0,0,0,,go back in the past and remember their greatness,\N{\rChinese}回溯过去，记住他们的伟大，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.10,0:41:02.00,English,,0,0,0,,they come together as an energetic, open, and cohesive society.\N{\rChinese}便会聚成一支活力十足、开放且团结的社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.28,0:41:08.06,English,,0,0,0,,So, yes, the Americans have this strategy\N{\rChinese}所以，没错，美国人确实有这个策略
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.06,0:41:12.64,English,,0,0,0,,that worked in Libya and Syria and other places, but it's not going to work in Iran.\N{\rChinese}那在利比亚、叙利亚等地奏效，但在伊朗却不会奏效。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.00,0:41:17.76,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's going to do the opposite in Iran.\N{\rChinese}实际上，它在伊朗会做相反的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.84,0:41:20.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And then you're like, well,\N{\rChinese}好吧？然后你会说，嗯，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.10,0:41:23.16,English,,0,0,0,,why don't the Americans not do this?\N{\rChinese}美国人为什么不这么做呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.42,0:41:26.18,English,,0,0,0,,And I already told you, because it is an empire, okay?\N{\rChinese}我已经告诉你了，因为它是一个帝国，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.58,0:41:28.84,English,,0,0,0,,It doesn't care about Iran, it cares about itself.\N{\rChinese}它不关心伊朗，关心的是自己。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.58,0:41:32.56,English,,0,0,0,,And so, it's sort of stuck with this policy, because, remember,\N{\rChinese}于是它就被这套政策卡住了，记得吗，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.70,0:41:36.02,English,,0,0,0,,it's trying to win this war as quickly as possible,\N{\rChinese}它正努力尽快赢得这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.14,0:41:40.16,English,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't have the manufactured capacity to fight this war for a long time.\N{\rChinese}因为它没有制造能力能持续作战
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.80,0:41:42.96,English,,0,0,0,,It's trying to reduce as many civilian casualties, sorry,\N{\rChinese}它正努力减少尽可能多的平民伤亡
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.04,0:41:46.14,English,,0,0,0,,it's trying to reduce as many casualties among its soldiers as possible,\N{\rChinese}它正努力尽可能减少士兵伤亡
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.30,0:41:50.90,English,,0,0,0,,because the Americans don't want to fight this war, they don't have the political will to fight this war.\N{\rChinese}因为美国人不想打这场战争，缺乏政治意愿
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.06,0:41:53.92,English,,0,0,0,,Americans are trying to win this war cheaply and fast.\N{\rChinese}美国人正试图以低成本、快速赢得这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.32,0:41:56.18,English,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't, then Americans are in a lot of trouble.\N{\rChinese}如果不行，美国人就会陷入大麻烦。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.22,0:41:59.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense, guys? All right.\N{\rChinese}好的？这样说通吗，大家？好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.96,0:42:02.88,English,,0,0,0,,Let me now conclude,\N{\rChinese}现在让我来总结一下，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.62,0:42:08.04,English,,0,0,0,,oh, sorry, let me now discuss the Iranian strategy, okay?\N{\rChinese}哦，抱歉，让我现在来讨论伊朗的策略，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.18,0:42:13.02,English,,0,0,0,,So, what the Americans are using is a classic strategy called siege warfare.\N{\rChinese}于是美国人采用的就是经典的围攻战术。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.52,0:42:17.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Okay? Okay?\N{\rChinese}好？好？好？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.24,0:42:23.06,English,,0,0,0,,And so, what the Iranians are going to do is they're going to respond with a classic strategy called guerrilla warfare.\N{\rChinese}于是伊朗人将采取的就是经典的游击战术。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.80,0:42:31.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And guerrilla warfare, guys, it's this simple, it's hide and seek.\N{\rChinese}好？游击战术，大家，就是这么简单，藏身与寻找。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.88,0:42:37.48,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So, you come bomb me with all, everything you have, I'll just hide in my mountains.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，你们用全力轰炸我，我就藏在山里。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.04,0:42:40.02,English,,0,0,0,,And then when you leave, what am I going to do?\N{\rChinese}然后你们离开，我又该怎么办？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.08,0:42:42.66,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to attack your GCC countries.\N{\rChinese}我要攻击你们的海合组织国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.94,0:42:45.12,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to lob drones, rockets at you.\N{\rChinese}我要投掷无人机、火箭。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.28,0:42:47.86,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to lob rockets at Israel, okay?\N{\rChinese}我要投掷火箭到以色列，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.86,0:42:50.70,English,,0,0,0,,I don't have, I don't have to strike that hard,\N{\rChinese}我没必要打得这么猛，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.98,0:42:53.04,English,,0,0,0,,I just have to make, I just have to be a pain in the ass, okay?\N{\rChinese}我只要制造点麻烦，搞点小麻烦，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.24,0:42:55.68,English,,0,0,0,,Because then, what happens is you're forced to come back and\N{\rChinese}于是你们就得回去应战，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.68,0:43:00.14,English,,0,0,0,,bomb the living hell out of me, but guess what, I'll just hide in my mountains again, it's hide and seek, okay?\N{\rChinese}把我炸成地狱吧，但你猜怎么了，我又会躲进山里，像捉迷藏一样，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.94,0:43:03.88,English,,0,0,0,,So, Iran can do this for years, and years,\N{\rChinese}于是伊朗可以这样做多年，几年，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.00,0:43:08.40,English,,0,0,0,,and years, but again, remember, America is forced to win this war as fast as possible,\N{\rChinese}几年，然而记得，阿美必须尽快赢得这场战争，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.56,0:43:10.12,English,,0,0,0,,because there is no political will,\N{\rChinese}因为没有政治意愿，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.76,0:43:12.82,English,,0,0,0,,they don't have manufacturing capacity,\N{\rChinese}他们没有制造能力，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.26,0:43:16.34,English,,0,0,0,,and they don't want to,\N{\rChinese}他们也不想这么做。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.44,0:43:19.04,English,,0,0,0,,they don't want that many cats, they don't want to do any casualties, and they can make damage, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们不想有那么多的猫，他们不想造成任何伤亡，而且他们能造成损失，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.42,0:43:21.86,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense, guys? Alright, so\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗，大家？好吧，接下来是这样：
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.86,0:43:24.90,English,,0,0,0,,that's all Iran's going to do, Iran's just going to be a pain in the ass, okay?\N{\rChinese}这就是伊朗要做的全部，伊朗只会是个麻烦，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.04,0:43:26.58,English,,0,0,0,,A pain in the ass.\N{\rChinese}一个麻烦
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.78,0:43:30.88,English,,0,0,0,,It's trying to create as much economic damage as possible, it's trying to create as much fear as possible,\N{\rChinese}它正试图造成尽可能多的经济损失，正试图制造尽可能多的恐慌。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.06,0:43:32.40,English,,0,0,0,,alright?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.60,0:43:34.42,English,,0,0,0,,Which will force America to attack.\N{\rChinese}这将迫使美国发动攻击。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.88,0:43:38.20,English,,0,0,0,,The grand question is this,\N{\rChinese}大问题是这个，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.46,0:43:42.96,English,,0,0,0,,will America launch a ground invasion, okay?\N{\rChinese}美国会发动陆战吗，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.16,0:43:47.82,English,,0,0,0,,Because if it does, then I'll be in the middle of a war.\N{\rChinese}因为如果那样做，我就会陷入战争之中。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.82,0:43:49.90,English,,0,0,0,,And, um, they've lost the war, okay?\N{\rChinese}而且，他们已经输了战争，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.54,0:43:53.64,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? Because, look, look, look at Iran, okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？因为，看看，看看伊朗，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.94,0:43:56.02,English,,0,0,0,,Mountains and mountains, deserts,\N{\rChinese}山山山，沙沙沙，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.02,0:44:00.54,English,,0,0,0,,it is impossible to occupy this country,\N{\rChinese}它占领这个国家不可能，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.76,0:44:03.30,English,,0,0,0,,alright?\N{\rChinese}好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.42,0:44:06.30,English,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to invade, and what Iran does want to do,\N{\rChinese}不可能入侵，伊朗想做的事，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.44,0:44:09.02,English,,0,0,0,,is be so, such a pain in the ass,\N{\rChinese}就是这样，真是个大麻烦，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.24,0:44:11.70,English,,0,0,0,,to commit so much guerrilla warfare, that\N{\rChinese}去发动这么多游击战，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.70,0:44:14.40,English,,0,0,0,,America is forced to invade, okay,\N{\rChinese}美国被迫入侵，好吗，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.46,0:44:17.36,English,,0,0,0,,from over here, and from over here, and from over here,\N{\rChinese}从这里开始，从那里开始，从这里开始，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.44,0:44:20.40,English,,0,0,0,,and from over here, and from over here, and over here and then eventually uh\N{\rChinese}从那里开始，从这里开始，从那里开始，最终……
